         <abstract>
            <p>This paper describes the current European method of regulating passenger car brake balance and examines the problems faced by manufacturers if a similar regulation were incorporated into the U.S. FMVSS system along with stopping distance requirements, as has been proposed as part of international brake regulation harmonization. A possible solution is discussed along with suggestions for its further consideration.</p>
